description: Archie gets a love letter from someone, and both Betty and Veronica swear it wasn't from them.
name: Love Showdown, Part 1

description: Archie is a typical small-town teenager. Generous, well-mannered, but clumsy, he is genuinely liked by many of his friends. Archie goes crazy when he sees an attractive girl, but mainly dates Veronica Lodge and Betty Cooper. He has taken various employment, but despite the best intentions, often clumsily breaks things, coming in conflict with Veronica's father Hiram Lodge and Riverdale High's principal, Waldo Weatherbee. As the lead singer of The Archies, Archie performs with Betty, Veronica, Reggie, and Jughead.
Can even Power Man and Iron Fist hope to stand against the cybernetically powered exo-skeleton of Doombringer?
name: The Armageddon Game

description: There's a new super hero in town by the name of Crime Buster. And, he's horning in on the Heroes for Hire's gig. Can Luke Cage and Iron Fist handle the competition?
name: Competition!

description: Power Man and Iron Fist battle the swirling villainy of the man called Whirlwind.
name: ...And an Ill Wind Shall Come!

description: Power Man and Iron Fist save a young man from the Hammer of Judgement, and more importantly, should they?
name: The Hammer of Judgement

description: When the Heroes for Hire and their friends attempt to celebrate a moment of happiness, their party is broken up by the hideous creature known as the Reaper.
name: Slime Street

description: A troubled teen with a gun takes refuge in a church after he accidentally kills a police officer. Unfortunately, more than just the cops are looking for him. A friend of the cop wants revenge. The Heroes For Hire are called in to defuse the situation before it gets even worse in this stand-alone story.
name: His Name--The Reaper! His Mission...Vengeance!

description: When Power Man and Iron Fist are hired to escort a young woman to her prom they wind up battling half the super villains in their rogues gallery.
name: O Deadly Debutante!

description:
Power Man and Iron Fist are in K'un L'un to find a cure for Iron Fist's radiation posioning. Accompanied by Colleen Wing, Luke and Danny find the city in ruins. This issue focuses on the team fighting Chiantang - the brother of the dragon king, who can assume both human and dragon form.

Feeling guilt for causing Chiantang's recent devestation of K'un L'un, Iron Fist's costume turns red, and he's out of control.

This issue marks the last appearance of the "real" Iron Fist and his replacement with a doppelganger who would appear to the finasl issue of the series.
name: DragonSlayer!

description: Iron Fist battles ninjas and S.M.I.L.E. agents to seek answers for the guilt he's felt over being responsible for thousands of deaths due to his gaining the power of the Iron Fist.
name: Crossfire

description: It's the end of the road for the Heroes for Hire and crazy John Lumas wants to make sure they go out with a bang. And can it be...Luke Cage is accused of the murder of Danny Rand? Plus, Twelve year old Bobby Wright's (Captain Hero) condition gets steadily worse. Can the chi of Iron Fist save the boy? In this issue witness the tragic death of two heroes. All this plus Power Man and Iron Fist take on the 1985 Super Bowl Campions the Chicago Bears in a football game.
name: HARDBALL
